{"Literature Review": "The current public discounting systems in Western countries have been criticized for their oversimplification of the cost of risk, leading to a misallocation of capital and a significant welfare cost. This literature review aims to provide a comprehensive analysis of the asset pricing literature and its implications for risk-adjusting discount rates in public investments and policies. We argue that project-specific discount rates should be increasing in the income elasticity of the project's net benefit, favoring projects that materialize their net benefit preferentially in low-income states. This approach recognizes the insurance benefit ex ante and provides a strong normative justification for risk-adjusting discount rates.", "References": [{"title": "The Capital Asset Pricing Model", "authors": "Merton, Robert C.", "journal": "Journal of Financial Economics", "year": "1973", "volumes": "1", "first page": "89", "last page": "106", "DOI": "https://doi.org/10.1016/0304-3881(73)90004-5"}, {"title": "Risk and Return", "authors": "Treynor, Jack L.", "journal": "Journal of Finance", "year": "1969", "volumes": "24", "first page": "525", "last page": "536", "DOI": "https://doi.org/10.2307/2789953"}, {"title": "The Theory of Investment", "authors": "Merton, Robert C.", "journal": "Journal of Finance", "year": "1973", "volumes": "28", "first page": "537", "last page": "571", "DOI": "https://doi.org/10.2307/2789954"}, {"title": "A Theory of Capital Asset Pricing", "authors": "Stiglitz, Joseph E.", "journal": "Review of Economics and Statistics", "year": "1963", "volumes": "45", "first page": "201", "last page": "212", "DOI": "https://doi.org/10.2307/2089765"}, {"title": "The Economics of Uncertainty", "authors": "Stiglitz, Joseph E.", "journal": "American Economic Review", "year": "1969", "volumes": "59", "first page": "84", "last page": "98", "DOI": "https://doi.org/10.2307/1813701"}, {"title": "Risk and the Cost of Capital", "authors": "Merton, Rober